LEMON SQUARES
6 Tbsp butter or margarine	1/4 tsp finely shredded lemon peel
1 c sugar, divided		3 Tbsp lemon juice
1/4 tsp salt			1/4 tsp baking powder
1 c + 2 Tbsp all-purpose flour	powdered sugar (optional)
2 eggs
 
Grease an 8x8x2 baking pan.  Beat butter for 30 seconds.  Add 1/4 c
sugar and salt, beating until fluffy.  Stir in 1 c flour.  Pat dough
onto bottom of pan.  Bake at 350 for 15 minutes.  Meanwhile, beat
eggs.  Add remaining 3/4 c sugar, 2 Tbsp flour, lemon peel, lemon
juice, and baking powder.  Beat 3 minutes or until slightly thickened.
Pour over baked layer.  Bake at 350 for 25 to 30 minutes or until
light golden brown around edges and center is set.  Cool.  Sift
powdered sugar over top if desired.  Cut into bars.










